init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Thus begins the story of the "Lost Generations" in this thought-provoking speculative sci-fi novel.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: To save their own lives, the Lost Generations develop technologies to prevent aging.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They build self-sustaining orbital habitats and highly automated underground cities, and develop gene therapy to eliminate aging.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And when the side effects finally came, they were prepared.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: were so terrible that all they could think of was death.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The Lucky Ones knew they needed to do something, anything, to end the suffering.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: After the death of the Lucky, the remaining Lost colonies began to form their own governments and figure out what to do next.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It was decided that they must not allow the same mistakes of their previous society to be repeated.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So they pulled the best, brightest and most intelligent minds from each of the remaining colonies.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And again, their efforts were successful.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But the strain of creating this drug took its toll on the minds and bodies of these remaining individuals, so they built a home for themselves in space where

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: they could work in peace and quiet on their next miracle drug.
